<br>
I wonder why?<br>
<br>
My personal view is that one can never quit EQ the only thing you can do is not play it for a while <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Hugs<br>
<br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198034">Intra</A> and <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157327">Sena</A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 478<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 2:30:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2221.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who post after quiting EQ</span><hr size=1> No life.  The investment of so much time in a game leaves the person realizing that they have no life once they leave.  So they continue to post how much we all suck for playing a game, when really they just want to keep on playing themselves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 3:06:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2221.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who post after quiting EQ</span><hr size=1> They want to play but have to justify to themselves why they stopped.  Putting it down makes themselves feel so much more elevated.  Just like the playground antics of children, they feel bigger because they think they made someone else littler.<br>
<br>
Oh... &amp;, yes, I have to admit I have a full on addiction.  I am going to GenCon in Aug &amp; started thinking about the fact I have to get the laptop prepped for EQ on the road.  I'm going to a -gaming- convention, a place to play -other- games &amp; I am thinking about how I can continue playing EQ there.... I think I need help (I might need to get a dial-up account for that weekend) *laugh*. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 852<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 4:15:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2221.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who post after quiting EQ</span><hr size=1> I'm NOT addicted to eq or AIR :-)<br>
<br>
Intra and Sena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=farnoak>Farnoak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 5:21:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2221.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who post after quiting EQ</span><hr size=1> They dislike the game but enjoy the community / friends?  The EQ boards are sometimes the only place where a decent concentration of people who you would otherwise totally lose touch with hang out online (besides in the game, of course).<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubanegrivm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banegrivm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 6:13:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2221.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People who post after quiting EQ</span><hr size=1> I quit, but I quit because I disliked the game mechanics in the end. I came to EQ originaly because I had heard about the dynamic role playing game. I do not feel I have found the table top feel here that was promised, and hence moved on. EQ and most MMORPG's are just not for me. That is just me, and my personal preferance.<br>
<br>
A good friend of mine in the fist of NWN still loves EQ to death. Thats his decision. But as to alot of generalities that get made about EverQuest players on the internet in circles of role playing tend to stereotype EQ'ers as Arios points out. However, consider this. Did not many that came here to FV come here to get away from the stereotypes of standard blue servers? Did not many come here for a more mature atmosphere?<br>
<br>
Personaly, I don't follow most EQ forums. I find myself wondering about the mentality, stability, or age level of most people on message boards for EQ let alone the interne. I think that the FV community is an oxymoron in a sense when it comes to communites in EQ, and I also do not think that FV fits anywhere near that schism either. People of FV should be proud of what it has. I occassionaly read the boards because i love table top gaming and gamers, and I occassionaly find a few good ongoing discussions about it.<br>
<br>
On a final note, I didn't leave my friends behind when I finally decided to hang my hat up. I still keep in touch pretty much with them, and generally if I ever hear from an old friend out of the blue I always make time for them or try to stop and help them out if they need it. <br>
<br>
I think FV is the best server, period. It has alot of things many servers will never see. A sense of community, maturity, and Captain Roleplay <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>Sovereign Lord of the <a href=http://www.1stfistoflight.com>1st Fist of Light</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 7:20:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2221.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well, I didn't post when I was cancelled ..</span><hr size=1> .. but I do post here more than anywhere else, even though I don't play on FV anymore.  I like the board.  Also, I will no doubt return someday, too. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
